{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783433600109,"sessionID":"ses_0c31ab9f9ffeQ78106pyBoIj54","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Ulz3MCGtIJJaLDN5S6UBL0DP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-001.md\n+# Iteration 001: Traceability Current-State Alignment\n+\n+## Focus\n+Reviewed target packet docs for contradictions between planned, completed, and resume-state surfaces.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: traceability, correctness\n+- Files reviewed: 8\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=2 P2=1\n+- New findings ratio: 0.35\n+\n+## Findings\n+### P1, Required\n+- **F001**: `plan.md` still marks completed migration work as pending. Definition of Done and phases list unchecked core work such as moved folders, rewritten references, validation, docs reconciliation, and tracking-folder commit [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/plan.md:61]. This contradicts the completion baseline in `tasks.md` and `implementation-summary.md` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/tasks.md:119] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/implementation-summary.md:25].\n+- **F002**: Packet frontmatter still routes resume to dispatch the review loop and reports `completion_pct: 0` in multiple docs [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/spec.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/plan.md:16] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/checklist.md:16] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/decision-record.md:15]. This conflicts with `implementation-summary.md` saying no safe action remains except deferred indexing and `completion_pct: 100` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/implementation-summary.md:15] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/implementation-summary.md:25].\n+\n+### P2, Suggestion\n+- **F003**: `graph-metadata.json` still reports derived status `in_progress` for the tracking packet [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/graph-metadata.json:43], while the implementation summary records completion [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/implementation-summary.md:25].\n+\n+## Claim Adjudication Packets\n+```json\n+{\"findingId\":\"F001\",\"claim\":\"plan.md exposes pending core migration work after the packet's task and implementation-summary surfaces claim completion.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/plan.md:61\",\".opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/tasks.md:119\",\".opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/implementation-summary.md:25\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Checked plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md, and validation output for a documented reason that plan checkboxes intentionally remain pending.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"The plan may preserve original intended tasks, but this packet uses plan.md Definition of Done as current completion metadata, so unchecked core items mislead resume/completion gates.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.9,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"If plan.md explicitly documents these unchecked boxes as historical baseline rather than current state.\"}\n+```\n+```json\n+{\"findingId\":\"F002\",\"claim\":\"frontmatter continuity in several canonical docs still instructs resume to dispatch the review loop despite completion metadata saying no action remains.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/spec.md:17\",\".opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/checklist.md:16\",\".opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/implementation-summary.md:15\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Compared all canonical spec-doc frontmatter continuity blocks against implementation-summary continuity and body evidence.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Some frontmatter may be stale and non-authoritative, but resume tooling reads these surfaces, making the drift operationally relevant.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.88,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"If resume tooling ignores these frontmatter continuity blocks for completed packets.\"}\n+```\n+\n+## Cross-Reference Results\n+| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n+|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n+| spec_code | partial | hard | plan.md:61, implementation-summary.md:25 | Current-state claims disagree. |\n+| checklist_evidence | partial | hard | checklist.md:67 | Deferred to later pass. |\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Validate generated metadata and track-root surfaces.\n+Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-002.md\n+# Iteration 002: Metadata Maintainability\n+\n+## Focus\n+Reviewed generated metadata and resume status surfaces.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: maintainability\n+- Files reviewed: 3\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n+- Refined findings: P2=1\n+- New findings ratio: 0.00\n+\n+## Findings\n+No new findings. Refined **F003**: stale generated status is advisory because the tracking folder validates with zero errors, but it still weakens resume/search trust [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/graph-metadata.json:43].\n+\n+## Cross-Reference Results\n+| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n+|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n+| spec_code | partial | hard | graph-metadata.json:43 | Metadata state still disagrees with implementation summary. |\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Check old-path and live metadata correctness.\n+Review verdict: PASS\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+# Iteration 003: Live Path Correctness\n+\n+## Focus\n+Sampled old migration path fragments and live JSON metadata for stale active references.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: correctness\n+- Files reviewed: 4\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n+- New findings ratio: 0.00\n+\n+## Findings\n+No new findings. The sampled stale-reference search found historical manifest/provenance mentions only, and no live JSON metadata hit for the sampled old paths [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/context-index.md:16].\n+\n+## Ruled Out\n+- Historical references in migration manifests are not defects because the packet intentionally documents source paths [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/spec.md:83].\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Review track map status.\n+Review verdict: PASS\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-004.md\n+# Iteration 004: Track Map Traceability\n+\n+## Focus\n+Reviewed the parent track's phase map against the completed tracking packet.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: traceability\n+- Files reviewed: 2\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=1\n+- New findings ratio: 0.04\n+\n+## Findings\n+### P2, Suggestion\n+- **F004**: Parent track phase map still lists `000-migration-from-system-speckit/` as `In Progress` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/spec.md:95], while the tracking packet's implementation summary says completion is 100% [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/implementation-summary.md:25].\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Security non-applicability and scope boundaries.\n+Review verdict: PASS\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-005.md\n+# Iteration 005: Security Boundary\n+\n+## Focus\n+Checked whether the spec-folder migration review exposes secrets, auth, sandbox, or executable trust-boundary risks.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: security\n+- Files reviewed: 4\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n+- New findings ratio: 0.00\n+\n+## Findings\n+No security findings. The checklist explicitly marks security N/A because the packet moves spec-doc folders and does not touch secrets, auth, or input-validation surfaces [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/checklist.md:90].\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Checklist evidence wording.\n+Review verdict: PASS\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-006.md\n+# Iteration 006: Checklist Evidence Gate\n+\n+## Focus\n+Reviewed checked P0/P1 checklist evidence and completion claims.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: traceability\n+- Files reviewed: 2\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n+- New findings ratio: 0.00\n+\n+## Findings\n+No new findings. Checklist evidence is mostly present, but the validation wording needs a separate advisory pass because the same rows say \"clean\" while recording non-zero accepted errors [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/checklist.md:67].\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Validation wording precision.\n+Review verdict: PASS\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-007.md\n+# Iteration 007: Validation Wording Precision\n+\n+## Focus\n+Reviewed validation claims for exactness against recorded evidence.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: maintainability, traceability\n+- Files reviewed: 2\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=1\n+- New findings ratio: 0.04\n+\n+## Findings\n+### P2, Suggestion\n+- **F005**: Checklist labels the track validation item as \"clean\" while the same row records `Errors: 2` accepted limitations [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/checklist.md:67]. The implementation summary uses clearer wording by listing the same two errors as known/accepted rather than clean [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/implementation-summary.md:91].\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Stabilization pass across all active findings.\n+Review verdict: PASS\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-008.md\n+# Iteration 008: Stabilization Replay\n+\n+## Focus\n+Replayed active F001-F005 evidence and searched for severity escalation.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: correctness, traceability\n+- Files reviewed: 6\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n+- New findings ratio: 0.00\n+\n+## Findings\n+No new findings. F001 and F002 remain active P1; no P0 impact found because migration outputs appear present and sampled live JSON old-path checks did not reveal active stale metadata.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Broaden to parent packet validation claims.\n+Review verdict: PASS\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-skill-advisor/000-migration-from-system-speckit/review/lineages/gpt-2/iterations/iteration-009.md\n+# Iteration 009: Parent Validation Claims\n+\n+## Focus\n+Compared packet claims about 026/027/028 validation to observed validation classes.\n+\n+## Scorecard\n+- Dimensions covered: correctness\n+- Files reviewed: 3\n+- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n+- New findings ratio: 0.00\n+\n+## Findings\n+No new finding. The packet records non-zero accepted/pre-existing errors for `system-skill-advisor` and `028`, so the current defec